/**
 * FDA disclaimer required alongside Biote symptom-awareness language
 * (CLAUDE.md hard constraint 3; BUILD_SPEC §7.8). Injected by
 * TreatmentLayout when content flags `bioteDisclaimer: true`.
 *
 * {{BIOTE_FDA_DISCLAIMER}} RESOLVED 2026-07-22 (operator-authorized, see
 * docs/DECISIONS.md): the wording below is Biote's own, transcribed from
 * the printed patient brochure. It previously rendered as a visible
 * placeholder token on /services/hormone-optimization — the one
 * disclosure §7.8 makes mandatory was never actually shown.
 *
 * The sentence names the four verbs the `disease-claims` category bans,
 * so it is enumerated verbatim in compliance/banned-patterns.json
 * `allowedStrings` — the fourth authorization, and the first for text a
 * regulator requires rather than copy the client wants.
 *
 * Two editing rules for whoever touches this next:
 *   1. The sentence must stay on ONE source line. lint-claims.mjs strips
 *      allowed strings and applies patterns per line, so a wrapped
 *      sentence matches nothing and trips every banned verb in it.
 *   2. Do not restate those verbs anywhere else in this file. Only the
 *      exact allowlisted sentence is stripped before the scan.
 */
const FDA_DISCLAIMER =
  'These statements have not been evaluated by the Food and Drug Administration. These products are not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease.';
---

<aside class="notice" role="note" aria-label="FDA disclosure">
